---
import Content from '../layouts/Content.astro';
---
<Content title="Rules" description="Community guidelines for The Kaamo Club.">
  <p>
    <em>
      Placeholder rules. Replace with whatever fits the community. The
      structure below is a starting point — keep, edit, or rewrite as you see
      fit.
    </em>
  </p>

  <h2>1. Be decent to each other</h2>
  <p>
    No harassment, slurs, or personal attacks. Disagree about ships, builds,
    and lore all you want — keep it about the topic, not the person.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Stay on topic</h2>
  <p>
    This is a Galaxy on Fire community. Off-topic chat is fine in the right
    spaces, but don't drown out the game-related discussion.
  </p>

  <h2>3. No spoilers without warning</h2>
  <p>
    Use spoiler tags or clear warnings for plot points and quest details from
    any of the games, especially for newer players working through them for
    the first time.
  </p>

  <h2>4. No pirated content distribution</h2>
  <p>
    Game preservation and discussion are welcome; redistributing copyrighted
    builds or paid DLC isn't. If you're not sure where the line is, ask a mod
    before posting.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Listen to the mods</h2>
  <p>
    The admins moderate in good faith. If you disagree with a decision, take
    it up in DMs rather than in public threads.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>Reporting and contact</h2>
  <p>
    If you see something that breaks these rules, ping any admin in Discord or
    drop a message to the contact email listed in the
    <a href="/datenschutz">Datenschutzerklärung</a>.
  </p>
</Content>
